cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the task of predicting various traits of a person given an image of their face, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and the proposed novel approach for incorporating facial landmark information also suggest the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the subjective traits predicted in the paper, such as emotions and attractiveness, may have implications in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
